hook.real_world_problem:
A competitor discovers Razorpay's payment status API and writes a scraper:

```
10:00:00 — bot fires 1,000 requests/second to GET /api/payments/{id}
10:00:01 — HikariCP pool (20 connections) exhausted
10:00:01 — real payment processing requests start timing out
10:00:02 — merchants begin calling support: 'payments not working'
10:00:30 — engineers page: DB at 100% CPU, 503s everywhere
```

The scraper costs ₹0. The damage: hours of downtime.

**The fix — Redis INCR rate limiting:**
```java
// Every request: INCR rate:merchant:{id}:minute:{currentMinute}
// If counter > 100: return HTTP 429 Too Many Requests

@Component
public class RateLimitFilter implements Filter {
    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain) {
        String merchantId = extractMerchantId(req);
        if (!rateLimiter.isAllowed(merchantId)) {
            HttpServletResponse http = (HttpServletResponse) res;
            http.setStatus(429);
            http.setHeader("Retry-After", "60");  // try again in 60 seconds
            http.getWriter().write("{\"error\": \"Rate limit exceeded\"}");
            return;
        }
        chain.doFilter(req, res);
    }
}
```

```
With rate limiting:
  Legitimate merchant: 50 req/min → all pass through
  Scraper bot: 1,000 req/min → first 100 pass, 900 get 429
  DB load: protected
  Real users: unaffected
```

One filter. Zero performance impact on legitimate traffic.

concept_explanation.fixed_window_counter:
**Fixed window counter — the simplest Redis rate limiter:**

```java
@Service
public class FixedWindowRateLimiter {
    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redis;

    FixedWindowRateLimiter(RedisTemplate<String,String> r) { redis = r; }

    /**
     * Returns true if the request is allowed.
     * Key: rate:{identifier}:{windowMinute}
     * Example: rate:merchant:M001:2024-06-15-14-23
     *          rate:ip:192.168.1.1:2024-06-15-14-23
     */
    public boolean isAllowed(String identifier, int maxRequests) {
        // Build key: unique per identifier per minute window
        long minuteWindow = System.currentTimeMillis() / 60_000;  // minute number since epoch
        String key = "rate:" + identifier + ":" + minuteWindow;

        // Atomic INCR: increment and get new count in one operation
        Long count = redis.opsForValue().increment(key);

        if (count == 1) {
            // First request in this window — set TTL so key auto-cleans
            redis.expire(key, Duration.ofMinutes(2));  // 2 min: covers edge case at window boundary
        }

        return count <= maxRequests;
    }

    // Remaining requests in current window:
    public long getRemainingRequests(String identifier, int maxRequests) {
        long minuteWindow = System.currentTimeMillis() / 60_000;
        String key = "rate:" + identifier + ":" + minuteWindow;
        Object current = redis.opsForValue().get(key);
        long used = current != null ? Long.parseLong(current.toString()) : 0;
        return Math.max(0, maxRequests - used);
    }

    // Time until window resets (in seconds):
    public long secondsUntilReset(String identifier) {
        long now = System.currentTimeMillis();
        long nextWindowStart = (now / 60_000 + 1) * 60_000;
        return (nextWindowStart - now) / 1000;
    }
}
```

**Key anatomy:**
```
rate : merchant : M001 : 28543210
  ↑       ↑        ↑        ↑
prefix  type    entity   minute number since epoch

'rate:ip:192.168.1.1:28543210'
'rate:user:U001:28543210'
'rate:endpoint:search:28543210'
```

**Why INCR is atomic:**
```
Thread A: INCR rate:M001:28543210  → 1
Thread B: INCR rate:M001:28543210  → 2 (not 1 again!)
Thread C: INCR rate:M001:28543210  → 3
// Redis is single-threaded: INCRs are serialized
// No two threads can both get the same count
// Compare: if you read-then-increment in Java, TWO threads can both read 0 and both get 1
```

concept_explanation.spring_filter:
**Spring Filter for rate limiting:**

```java
import jakarta.servlet.*;
import jakarta.servlet.http.*;
import org.springframework.core.annotation.Order;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;

@Component
@Order(1)  // run before other filters
public class RateLimitFilter implements Filter {

    private final FixedWindowRateLimiter limiter;

    RateLimitFilter(FixedWindowRateLimiter l) { limiter = l; }

    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain)
            throws IOException, ServletException {

        HttpServletRequest  httpReq = (HttpServletRequest)  req;
        HttpServletResponse httpRes = (HttpServletResponse) res;

        // Extract identifier (user ID, API key, or IP):
        String apiKey = httpReq.getHeader("X-API-Key");
        String identifier = apiKey != null ? "apikey:" + apiKey
                                           : "ip:" + getClientIp(httpReq);

        // Check rate limit (100 req/min for API keys, 20/min for IP):
        int limit = apiKey != null ? 100 : 20;

        if (!limiter.isAllowed(identifier, limit)) {
            // HTTP 429 Too Many Requests:
            httpRes.setStatus(429);
            httpRes.setContentType("application/json");
            httpRes.setHeader("Retry-After",         String.valueOf(limiter.secondsUntilReset(identifier)));
            httpRes.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Limit",   String.valueOf(limit));
            httpRes.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Remaining","0");
            httpRes.getWriter().write(
                "{\"error\":\"Rate limit exceeded\"," +
                "\"limit\":" + limit + "," +
                "\"retryAfterSeconds\":" + limiter.secondsUntilReset(identifier) + "}"
            );
            return;  // stop filter chain — don't forward to controller!
        }

        // Add remaining quota headers to successful responses:
        long remaining = limiter.getRemainingRequests(identifier, limit);
        httpRes.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Limit",     String.valueOf(limit));
        httpRes.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Remaining", String.valueOf(remaining));

        chain.doFilter(req, res);  // forward to controller
    }

    private String getClientIp(HttpServletRequest req) {
        // Check X-Forwarded-For for reverse proxy setups:
        String forwarded = req.getHeader("X-Forwarded-For");
        if (forwarded != null && !forwarded.isBlank()) {
            return forwarded.split(",")[0].trim();
        }
        return req.getRemoteAddr();
    }
}

concept_explanation.per_endpoint_limits:
**Per-endpoint rate limiting — different limits for different APIs:**

```java
@Service
public class TieredRateLimiter {
    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redis;

    // Different limits per endpoint type:
    private static final Map<String, Integer> ENDPOINT_LIMITS = Map.of(
        "/api/payments",        50,   // payment creation: 50/min (sensitive)
        "/api/payments/status", 200,  // status check: 200/min (read-only)
        "/api/search",          100,  // search: 100/min
        "/api/reports",         10    // reports: 10/min (expensive)
    );

    public boolean isAllowed(String userId, String endpoint) {
        // Find matching limit (prefix match for parameterized routes):
        int limit = ENDPOINT_LIMITS.entrySet().stream()
            .filter(e -> endpoint.startsWith(e.getKey()))
            .mapToInt(Map.Entry::getValue)
            .findFirst()
            .orElse(200);  // default: 200/min

        long window = System.currentTimeMillis() / 60_000;
        // Key includes ENDPOINT: different limits per path!
        String key = "rate:" + userId + ":" + endpoint.replace('/', ':') + ":" + window;

        Long count = redis.opsForValue().increment(key);
        if (count == 1) redis.expire(key, Duration.ofMinutes(2));

        return count <= limit;
    }

    // Razorpay-style: also limit per merchant per operation:
    public boolean isPaymentAllowed(String merchantId) {
        return isAllowed("merchant:" + merchantId, "/api/payments");
    }

    public boolean isRefundAllowed(String merchantId) {
        long window = System.currentTimeMillis() / 60_000;
        String key = "rate:refund:" + merchantId + ":" + window;
        Long count = redis.opsForValue().increment(key);
        if (count == 1) redis.expire(key, Duration.ofMinutes(2));
        return count <= 10;  // 10 refunds per minute max
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.sliding_window_log:
**Sliding window log — more accurate, higher memory cost:**

```java
// Fixed window problem:
// Window 1: 00:00 - 00:59 — user makes 100 requests at 00:58
// Window 2: 01:00 - 01:59 — user makes 100 requests at 01:01
// In the 4 seconds between 00:58 and 01:01: 200 requests!
// Fixed window can't see across window boundaries.

// Sliding window with Redis ZSet:
@Service
public class SlidingWindowRateLimiter {
    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redis;

    SlidingWindowRateLimiter(RedisTemplate<String,String> r) { redis = r; }

    public boolean isAllowed(String identifier, int maxRequests, Duration window) {
        String key = "sw:" + identifier;
        long now = System.currentTimeMillis();
        long windowStart = now - window.toMillis();

        // Remove requests older than the window:
        redis.opsForZSet().removeRangeByScore(key, 0, windowStart);

        // Count requests in the current window:
        Long count = redis.opsForZSet().zCard(key);

        if (count != null && count >= maxRequests) {
            return false;  // rate limit exceeded
        }

        // Add this request with current timestamp as score:
        redis.opsForZSet().add(key, String.valueOf(now), now);
        redis.expire(key, window.multipliedBy(2));  // cleanup

        return true;
    }
    // Tradeoff: more memory (stores every request timestamp)
    // vs Fixed window: O(1) per request, no cross-boundary spike issue
    // For most APIs: fixed window is sufficient
}
```

step_by_step_solution.details:
```java
@Service
public class RazorpayRateLimiter {
    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redis;

    RazorpayRateLimiter(RedisTemplate<String,String> r) { redis = r; }

    public RateLimitResult check(String merchantId, String endpoint) {
        int limit = endpointLimit(endpoint);
        long window = System.currentTimeMillis() / 60_000;
        String key = "rate:" + merchantId + ":" + endpoint + ":" + window;

        Long count = redis.opsForValue().increment(key);
        if (count == 1) redis.expire(key, Duration.ofMinutes(2));

        long remaining = Math.max(0, limit - count);
        long resetIn   = secondsUntilNextMinute();

        return new RateLimitResult(count <= limit, count, limit, remaining, resetIn);
    }

    private int endpointLimit(String ep) {
        if (ep.contains("/payments") && !ep.contains("/status")) return 100;
        if (ep.contains("/status")) return 500;
        if (ep.contains("/refunds")) return 20;
        return 200;
    }

    private long secondsUntilNextMinute() {
        long now = System.currentTimeMillis();
        return ((now / 60_000 + 1) * 60_000 - now) / 1000;
    }

    public record RateLimitResult(
        boolean allowed, long count, int limit, long remaining, long resetInSeconds) {}
}
```

```java
@Component @Order(1)
public class RazorpayRateLimitFilter implements Filter {
    private final RazorpayRateLimiter limiter;
    RazorpayRateLimitFilter(RazorpayRateLimiter l) { limiter = l; }

    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain)
            throws IOException, ServletException {
        HttpServletRequest  rq = (HttpServletRequest)  req;
        HttpServletResponse rs = (HttpServletResponse) res;

        String merchantId = rq.getHeader("X-Merchant-Id");
        if (merchantId == null) { chain.doFilter(req, res); return; }

        var result = limiter.check(merchantId, rq.getRequestURI());

        rs.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Limit",     String.valueOf(result.limit()));
        rs.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Remaining", String.valueOf(result.remaining()));
        rs.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Reset",     String.valueOf(result.resetInSeconds()));

        if (!result.allowed()) {
            rs.setStatus(429);
            rs.setContentType("application/json");
            rs.setHeader("Retry-After", String.valueOf(result.resetInSeconds()));
            rs.getWriter().write(
                String.format("{\"error\":\"Rate limit exceeded\"" +
                    ",\"limit\":%d,\"retryAfterSeconds\":%d}",
                    result.limit(), result.resetInSeconds()));
            return;
        }
        chain.doFilter(req, res);
    }
}
```

worked_example.final_code:
// INCR + EXPIRE: atomic counter that auto-cleans
// Filter @Order(1): runs before controllers; chain.doFilter proceeds or 429 returned
// RateLimitResult record: clean return type with all limit info
// X-RateLimit-Remaining: lets clients self-throttle before hitting limit
